This paper deals with clustering belief functions, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of metalevel evidence also suggests a connection to data mining (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper's focus on belief functions and their manipulation could also fit into the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
